<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer10366790080720590637">John Kennedy Toole was an American novelist from New Orleans, Louisiana, best known for his novel <i>A Confederacy of Dunces</i>.<br/><br/>Toole&apos;s novels remained unpublished during his lifetime. Some years after his death by suicide, Toole&apos;s mother brought the manuscript of <i>A Confederacy of Dunces</i> to the attention of the novelist Walker Percy, who ushered the book into print. In 1981 Toole was posthumously awarde</span>
  <span id="freeText10366790080720590637" style="display:none">John Kennedy Toole was an American novelist from New Orleans, Louisiana, best known for his novel <i>A Confederacy of Dunces</i>.<br /><br />Toole's novels remained unpublished during his lifetime. Some years after his death by suicide, Toole's mother brought the manuscript of <i>A Confederacy of Dunces</i> to the attention of the novelist Walker Percy, who ushered the book into print. In 1981 Toole was posthumously awarded the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction.<br /><br /></span>
